@weltkrieg_defeat

= Berlin on fire

Our forces are no match for those of the syndicalist and narodniks. Heer and allied armies are quickly overpowered by the forces of the Third Internationale and Moscow Accords. The fight is bloody and cruel, but it all ends quickly. Kaiser and his family flee the country, as the russian sword and thorns dominate Berlin's landscape from atop the Reichstag's ruins.

Germany is divided among the invaders, who seem to be preparing for another war, this time among each other. Soon, german soil will become a battlefield once more.

Our resistance will be recorded in the history books, and in the future, our names will be honored. But for now, all is lost.

- @game_over: Game over.

@weltkrieg_long_war

= Hohenzollerns flee the country!

Both sides are unwilling to go down without a fight and refuse to yield. The war devolves into battles of attrition, with massive armored operations supported by unprecedented artillery and aerial devastation wreaking havoc among soldiers of both sides. Month by month, Reichspakt armies are steadily pushed back on the eastern front by the seemingly endless russian onslaught, while our offensives in the west bring no concrete results. With victory seeming anything but possible and faith in victory waning every week, kaiser Wilhelm flees Germany for Mittelafrika, hoping to avoid persecution by the soon-to-be victors.

In response to this shameful display, [? if spd_in_government : SPD ?][? if not spd_in_government : DVLP ?] installs an interim president to lead the country for the duration of war.

As russian tanks overrun Minsk and Kiev, german cities in the east are being prepared for the looming threat of invasion. It seems our two decades of hegemony have passed.

- @d_day: Entente finally enters the stage.

@d_day

Our desperate resistance wasn't in vain at the end of the day. News of an Entente invasion of the British Isles and photos of the Union Jack waving over devastated Manchester mark a turning point in the Second Weltkrieg. With the so-called D-Day diverting british troops from the western front, reinvigorated Heer launches its final offensive into France. As Paris falls into german hands once more, the Third Internationale  declares unconditional surrender. Although it takes many more months and lives, Russians and their allies soon follow. 

- @game_over: Game over.

@kaiserreich_victory
achievement: weltkrieg_won

Thanks to extensive preparations and throughtout reforms conducted by our military, syndicalist and russian troops prove no match for the elite Heer units. Our foes quickly fall, and Germany seems to have secured its position of the master of the world.

- @game_over: Game over.